name: Christmas Lights
description:
The artwork story :
Christmas night, another fight, tears we cried a flood
Got all kinds of poison in, of poison in my blood
Took my feet to Oxford Street tryna right the wrongs
Just walk away those windows say but I can't believe she's gone

The breakup with my wife happened about a week before Christmas that year, made me cry a lot of tears. I was inconsolable at the time. I drank very heavily, put lots of poison in my blood. I was in London which makes the Oxford Street reference relatable. And I couldn't believe she was gone.

I have come out of it all the other side now and am much happier

digital painting 4014 x 1334 px
